{"key":"post-11121920","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>11121920</id>\n<content>You want to isolate strains from spores.&amp;nbsp; You grow each and every isolate to the fruiting stage, after taking samples of each mycelium and storing it in the refrigerator as soon as the isolate is made.&amp;nbsp; This way, you find your best performing strains, and then go back to your well-marked masters in refrigeration and get out the best one.&amp;nbsp; Keep and grow it for many years.&amp;nbsp; Discard the poor/non performers.&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Yes, you can get non-fruiting isolates.&amp;nbsp; You'll get some poor isolates, some good ones, and a few stellar ones.&amp;nbsp; Those are what you keep.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>11121926</next>\n<prev>11121193</prev>\n<first>11119531</first>\n<last>11122124</last>\n<when>1253848411</when>\n<utime>09/25/09 06:13 AM</utime>\n</post>"}